docstring:
"""
 This module contains functions that generate ctypes prototypes for the
 GDAL routines.
"""

functions.docstring: """Generate a ctypes function that returns a boolean value."""
functions.name: bool_output

functions.docstring: "Generate a ctypes function that returns a double value."
functions.name: double_output

functions.docstring:
"""
    Generate a function that returns a Geometry either by reference
    or directly (if the return_geom keyword is set to True).
    """
functions.name: geom_output

functions.docstring: "Generate a ctypes function that returns an integer value."
functions.name: int_output

functions.docstring: "Generate a ctypes function that returns a 64-bit integer value."
functions.name: int64_output

functions.docstring:
"""
    Generate a ctypes prototype for the given function with
    the given C arguments that returns a pointer to an OGR
    Spatial Reference System.
    """
functions.name: srs_output

functions.docstring:
"""
    Generate a ctypes prototype for the given function with the
    given argument types that returns a string from a GDAL pointer.
    The `const` flag indicates whether the allocated pointer should
    be freed via the GDAL library routine VSIFree -- but only applies
    only when `str_result` is True.
    """
functions.name: string_output

functions.docstring:
"""
    For functions that don't only return an error code that needs to
    be examined.
    """
functions.name: void_output

functions.docstring: """For functions that return a c_char_p array."""
functions.name: chararray_output
